static const base::String gaia::core::DropBoxManager::ACTION_DROPBOX_ENTRY_ADDED ( ) [static]

Broadcast Action: This is broadcast when a new entry is added in the dropbox.

You must hold the android.Manifest.permission#READ_LOGS permission in order to receive this broadcast.

This is a protected intent that can only be sent by the system.

void gaia::core::DropBoxManager::addText ( const base::String &  tag,
const base::String &  data

Stores human-readable text.

The data may be discarded eventually (or even immediately) if space is limited, or ignored entirely if the tag has been blocked (see isTagEnabled).

bool gaia::core::DropBoxManager::isTagEnabled ( const base::String &  tag)

Checks any blacklists (set in settings) to see whether a certain tag is allowed.

Entries with disabled tags will be dropped immediately, so you can save the work of actually constructing and sending the data.

Parameters:
tagthat would be used in addText or addFile
Returns:
whether events with that tag would be accepted
